item.title: About Me
item.content:encoded:
I pursued and earned my B.A. in Psychology and M.A. in Human Behavior. I hold an ACC credential through the International Coaching Federation (ICF), an internationally recognized organization that holds Coaches to an ethical high standard.

I’ve had the pleasure of coaching college professors, community leaders, business professionals, students, homemakers and more. I’m an instructor at an ICF accredited academy teaching students to be future life coaches. I believe that growth is not bound by age! In our journeys of life, we have the ability to gain the confidence, to be creative, be bold, to dream bigger, to take the next step! I hope you will let me continue to use my passion for people and co-journey with you down a path of discovery, learning, and growth.

item.title: About Life Coaching
item.content:encoded:
Coaching FAQs

What is Life Coaching?

When is the last time you had a TRUE conversation? One where you could speak with out holding back, be free to express yourself with out fear of judgement, and to be heard, truly heard. That’s what life coaching is. ICF Life Coaches are professionally trained to meet you where you are, assist you defining what’s next, and help you build a bridge between that gap. By asking the right questions, we aid our clients in moving forward to attain a greater and more fulfilling life.

What can you expect from me as your coach?

Life coaching differs from consulting, mentoring and therapy in that we do not direct or lead the clients we work with. Life Coaches let you be the champion of your own destiny through the creative partnership we form. You can expect powerful questioning to gain clarity, exploration of your vision and goals and challenges to help see things in a new perspectives. I am here to encourage you to the best version of yourself through self-discovery, growth and accountability.

What is expected of you as a client?

Be your authentic self! As your coach, I will not bring judgement or bias to our coaching relationship, giving you the freedom to be open in our sessions. Bring your willingness to change and be open to discover new things about yourself and your situation. Journey Life Coaching creates a safe space to facilitate your growth and change. You will be asked to follow through on actionable items between coaching sessions.

Have more questions?

Don’t hesitate to reach out to us. Journey Life Coaching is here to help!

item.title: Work With Me
item.content:encoded:
EVERY JOURNEY STARTS WITH A SINGLE STEP, TAKE YOURS TODAY!

Individual Coaching

You are the only focus in our individual coaching sessions. Our coaching sessions will help you clarify your thoughts and actions, reduce stress and anxiety, and create actionable steps. I provide accountability and tools that motivate you to move toward your next destination.

Journey Life Coaching is passionate about personal growth and development. We believe that as you tap into your potential, not only will you begin to grow and develop, you will thrive! Whether you want to move upward to the next level in your professional or personal life, as your Coach I am here to help you roadmap your path to a healthy, satisfying, successful life. Together we will co-create goals to:

  • Learn new things

  • Gain competence

  • Become proactive

  • Cultivate innate abilities

  • Improve time management

  • Develop a perseverance mindset

Life coaching addresses many issues we all deal with during our life’s journey. Whether your feeling stuck and unsatisfied, seeking your life’s purpose, or need to sort through ‘mental clutter’, coaching is right for you.

Self-Confidence & Empowerment Coaching

In coaching, we call the thieves of confidence and power “saboteurs’ and '“limiting beliefs’. We often harbor negative beliefs that we don’t recognize or know that we have. The term saboteurs and limiting beliefs refer to negative convictions held as truths that limit your thinking, behaviors, feelings and ultimately your life. They can be so strong that they hinder your life’s direction through self-judgement, self-doubt and self-sabotage. These false ideals restrict your:

  • Self-worth

  • Power

  • Growth

  • Voice

  • Self-esteem

During our Self-Confidence and Empowerment Coaching sessions, we identify and challenge the roadblocks of saboteurs and limiting beliefs you have about yourself and others. Our one-on-one sessions will focus on building your confidence and self-esteem, empowering your individual voice and creating a strong self-image. We co-journey together to eliminate self-sabotaging barriers and replace limiting beliefs with sound, new beliefs about yourself and others.

Group Coaching

Sometimes in life we find that need to journey with others. Group coaching brings together small, intimate groups of people in a conversational space. These groups are centered on subjects such as goal planning, building self-esteem, accountability, self-care, and more. In these group sessions, the group members thoughts, feelings and actions are the focus, not the coaches.

Benefits of group coaching include:

  • Group support and accountability

  • Renewed inspiration, creativity and growth

  • Connect with new people and build new relationships

  • Learning from fellow peers

  • Interact with others who may share the same or different views

All group coaching sessions are held in a safe, confidential environment where you can be your true authentic self without judgement or bias. Respect for others is held as a high priority within group coaching sessions.
